elementList.description: 2 bedroom flat in Alfama for rent Charming 2 bedroom flat in Alfama, tastefully furnished and fully equipped kitchen, with the privilege of 4 balconies and lovely river views. The building was fully recovered, preserving its ancient façade, the quality of materials can be seen inside the flats, where it mixes the modern style with the original charm of the building. The flat is fully furnished and equipped with high-end appliances. Cooktop, combined, hood, electric oven, dishwasher and washing machine, microwave oven, electric boiler, air conditioning hot and cold. It also has double glazing. It is located in the oldest district of Lisbon, with its Moorish origins, here where tradition still lives and breathes every day. Alfama is a very peculiar neighbourhood, resembling an old village not only in appearance but also having a relatively small and close community. The neighbourhood is frequented daily by Portuguese and foreign tourists. It is known for its restaurants and fado houses, as well as for the popular saints´ festivities, especially on the night of Santo António, Whoever lives here will not be able to resist getting involved with the most authentic and traditional of Lisbon. A few steps away from the São Vicente Church and the magnificent viewpoints of Graça, with their beautiful esplanades and enchanting gardens. A few steps away from the tram stations. Surrounded by spectacular viewpoints. The rent does not include services.   Rent conditions: two rents and a deposit, guarantor, minimum contract of one year.
